reserve C for (C_Measure of X);
theorem
Th17: ((A in ( sigma_Field C ) & B in ( sigma_Field C )) implies ( A \/ B ) in ( sigma_Field C ))
proof
assume that
A1: A in ( sigma_Field C )
and
A2: B in ( sigma_Field C );
reconsider A,B as (Subset of X) by A1,A2;
set D = ( A \/ B );
(for W,Z being (Subset of X) holds ((W c= D & Z c= ( X \ D )) implies ( ( C . W ) + ( C . Z ) ) = ( C . ( W \/ Z ) )))
proof
let W being (Subset of X),Z being (Subset of X);
assume that
A3: W c= D
and
A4: Z c= ( X \ D );
set W2 = ( W \ A );
set Z1 = ( W2 \/ Z );
A5: ( ( X \ A ) /\ ( X \ B ) ) c= ( X \ B ) by XBOOLE_1:17;
set W1 = ( W /\ A );
A6: W1 c= A by XBOOLE_1:17;
( ( X \ A ) /\ ( X \ B ) ) c= ( X \ A ) by XBOOLE_1:17;
then A7: ( X \ ( A \/ B ) ) c= ( X \ A ) by XBOOLE_1:53;
Z c= ( ( X \ A ) /\ ( X \ B ) ) by A4,XBOOLE_1:53;
then A8: Z c= ( X \ B ) by A5,XBOOLE_1:1;
W = ( W1 \/ W2 ) by XBOOLE_1:51;
then ( C . W ) <= ( ( C . W1 ) + ( C . W2 ) ) by CKB6:1;
then A9: ( ( C . W ) + ( C . Z ) ) <= ( ( ( C . W1 ) + ( C . W2 ) ) + ( C . Z ) ) by XXREAL_3:36;
( W \ A ) c= ( ( B \/ A ) \ A ) by A3,XBOOLE_1:33;
then A10: ( W \ A ) c= ( B \ A ) by XBOOLE_1:40;
( B \ A ) c= B by XBOOLE_1:36;
then W2 c= B by A10,XBOOLE_1:1;
then A11: ( ( C . W2 ) + ( C . Z ) ) <= ( C . Z1 ) by A2,A8,CKB5:def 1;
C is  nonnegative by CKB4:def 1;
then A12: ( 0. ) <= ( C . W1 ) by MEASURE1:def 2;
( W \ A ) c= ( X \ A ) by XBOOLE_1:33;
then ( W2 \/ Z ) c= ( ( X \ A ) \/ Z ) by XBOOLE_1:9;
then A13: Z1 c= ( X \ A ) by A4,A7,XBOOLE_1:1,XBOOLE_1:12;
( C . ( W \/ Z ) ) = ( C . ( ( W1 \/ W2 ) \/ Z ) ) by XBOOLE_1:51
.= ( C . ( W1 \/ Z1 ) ) by XBOOLE_1:4
.= ( ( C . W1 ) + ( C . Z1 ) ) by A1,A6,A13,CKB7:1;
then A14: ( ( C . W1 ) + ( ( C . W2 ) + ( C . Z ) ) ) <= ( C . ( W \/ Z ) ) by A11,XXREAL_3:36;
A15: C is  nonnegative by CKB4:def 1;
then A16: ( 0. ) <= ( C . Z ) by MEASURE1:def 2;
( 0. ) <= ( C . W2 ) by A15,MEASURE1:def 2;
then ( ( ( C . W1 ) + ( C . W2 ) ) + ( C . Z ) ) <= ( C . ( W \/ Z ) ) by A16,A12,A14,XXREAL_3:44;
then A17: ( ( C . W ) + ( C . Z ) ) <= ( C . ( W \/ Z ) ) by A9,XXREAL_0:2;
( C . ( W \/ Z ) ) <= ( ( C . W ) + ( C . Z ) ) by CKB6:1;
hence thesis by A17,XXREAL_0:1;
end;
hence thesis by CKB7:1;
